{
  "stem": "14060.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I already went to school from 1936 onwards.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And in the same street from the main square, which was called Szechenyi there, was the Jewish school.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Opposite was this gymnasium, which I went to later.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And behind it was a Catholic primary school and also up to the age of 14 school.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I remember very clearly that as we used to come out from school in my time, which was between 1936 and 1940, when I went to primary school, those children from Catholic school left school at the same time, 1 o'clock.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And there was constantly-- we were sort of fist-fight-wise, you know, like children do, attacked by sometime individual, sometime a group.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we used to carry leather school cases on our back.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I remember that we got into the practice of putting that on the other way, in others words, like a Roman shield in front of you and come out of school with our hands in gloves and ready for a fight.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It didn't happen very often.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It wasn't too serious.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It could have happened that if non-Jews would have stopped it, because they would not have been necessarily aware who was a Jew or wasn't, because it wasn't customary, in our part of the world, that people went with long beards and payos and children.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They were literally unrecognizable in the main, except for a few extremely religious families.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So even they could have stopped it, because it was just some disturbance on the street.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, there were no knives or no serious injuries.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it was the general norm of life.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And one accepted it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I mean, we lived approximately 15 to 20 minutes from the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And as a child, we always had bicycles.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
